{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17486963","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17486963"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T02:51:55+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T02:51:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"219"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"219","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/219"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.2,0.47,0.03,0.17,0.13]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"219"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"37359"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"219","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/219"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"219"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"22007"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"36"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"112"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"35"},{"type":"contributions","id":"153"},{"type":"contributions","id":"234"},{"type":"contributions","id":"4026"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37707"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"37359","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/37359"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 69-year-old man presents with a six month history of worsening nocturia, now getting up twice at night to pass urine. His medical history includes severe chronic obstructive pulmonary disease. He was diagnosed carcinoma of the prostate (small volume, Gleason 3+3 =6) recently, with no evidence of any metastatic spread. Since this diagnosis was established, he has been started on home oxygen for symptom-focussed management. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"With regards to his prostate cancer, which one of the following is the most appropriate management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Radical prostatectomy","Watchful waiting","Chemoradiotherapy","Androgen deprivation therapy","Radiotherapy"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient is not fit for any form of active intervention and perhaps even an annual digital rectal examination (DRE) and measurement of the prostate-specific antigen (PSA) might be over-treatment. \u003Cstrong\u003EWatchful waiting\u003C/strong\u003E is most appropriate for this medically unfit patient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf he was younger and fitter, \u0027active surveillance\u0027 might be more appropriate, when one of the options of \u003Cstrong\u003Eradiotherapy\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003Esurgery with radical prostatectomy\u003C/strong\u003E might be considered. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese patients would be in a close follow-up protocol, such as 3 - 4 monthly DRE/PSA, annual biopsies and MRIs. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf this patient\u0027s PSA did rise rapidly, \u003Cstrong\u003Eandrogen deprivation therapy\u003C/strong\u003E might be considered. \u003Cstrong\u003EChemoradiation\u003C/strong\u003E would only be considered if he had metastatic disease. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWith regards to the patient\u0027s lower urinary tract symptoms, these could be managed with an alpha blocker - he is not likely to be fit for a transurethral resection of his prostate (TURP) or \u003Cstrong\u003Eradical prostatectomy\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Active treatment of prostate cancer must be tempered against the general state of health of the patient."],"references":["Gordetsky, J. \u0026 Epstein, J.. 2016. Grading of prostatic adenocarcinoma: current state and prognostic implications. Diagn Pathol 11: 25. doi: 10.1186/s13000-016-0478-2.","Body A, Pranavan G, Tan TH, Slobodian P. Medical management of metastatic prostate cancer. Aust Prescr. 2018 Oct;41(5):154-159. doi: 10.18773/austprescr.2018.046. Epub 2018 Oct 2. PMID: 30410212; PMCID: PMC6202297."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"22007"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"219"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"22007","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/22007"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-06-28T14:10:18+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-03T05:54:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"219"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"37359"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"36","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/36"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd43","name":"Urology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id"